    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-04-04T17:30:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-04-04T17:30:00-05:00" n="744"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d744">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">852.00/9107: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Vice Consul at Valencia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wallner</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Valencia</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-04-04T18:00:00-04:30"
                            >April 4, 1939—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received April 4—4:50 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>40. Department’s telegram No. 26, March 30, 5 p.m. With the exception of 21
                    Communist members of the secret police already imprisoned by the National
                    Defense Council who were shot yesterday morning, no executions are believed yet
                    to have taken place in Valencia. Genuine efforts are being made to avoid acts of
                    privation [<hi rend="italic">reprisal?</hi>]. As the situation develops I shall
                    report further.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wallner</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
